===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|日|口|ls=ic|c1=s|c2=s|t1=sun|t2=mouth}}. The mouth is a reference to being awakened at dawn through shouts or songs. During the Warring States Period, {{zh-m|*口}} developed into {{zh-m|*曰}}.

===Etymology 1===
{{och-l|昌|tr=khlaŋ ~ thaŋ}} is possibly related to {{och-l|陽}}, in which case it would go back to *''khlaŋ'', supported by {{cog|mkh-vie-pro|*hlaŋᴮ}}; note the phonetic parallelism with {{och-l|唱|tr=k-hlaŋh}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

See {{zh-l|陽}} for further etymology.

